%I A391440 #19 Jun 11 2026 08:21:01
%S A391440 1,1,2,1,1,1,2,2,2,1,2,2,1,2,1,2,2,2,1,1,2,2,4,1,2,1,2,2,1,2,2,2,2,2,
%T A391440 2,1,2,2,4,1,1,2,4,2,1,2,1,1,2,4,2,1,2,2,2,2,2,1,4,2,2,1,1,2,2,4,1,4,
%U A391440 2,1,4,4,2,1,2,2,2,1,2,2,2,2,4,1,1,2,2,4,2,2,2,1,2,2,2,4,2,4
%N A391440 Number of genera in the order of real quadratic fields with discriminant A079896(n).
%C A391440 Number of elements that square to the identity in the form class group of discriminant D = A079896(n).
%H A391440 Jianing Song, <a href="/A391440/b391440.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A391440 Rick L. Shepherd, <a href="https://www.digitalgreensboro.org/record/14435">Binary quadratic forms and genus theory</a>, Master of Arts Thesis, University of North Carolina at Greensboro, 2013.
%F A391440 For D = A079896(n), a(n) = 2^(omega(|D|) - t), where omega = A001221, and t = 0 if 32|D, t = 2 if D == 4 (mod 16), t = 1 otherwise. See A391441.
%o A391440 (PARI) r(D) = omega(D) - if(D%32==0, 0, if(D%16==4, 2, 1)) \\ gives 2-rank of Cl+(D)
%o A391440 for(D=1, 1000, if(D%4<=1 && !issquare(D), print1(2^r(D), ", ")))
%Y A391440 Cf. A003640 (for imaginary quadratic fields).
%Y A391440 For a list of sequences related to the class groups of real quadratic fields, see A390079.
%K A391440 nonn,changed
%O A391440 1,3
%A A391440 _Jianing Song_, Dec 09 2025
